2026-03-08 | Check if Pythagorean Triplet Exists

	Question
Return true if such a triplet exists in the array, otherwise return false.

	Approach
1.	Square all elements in the array.
2.	Sort the array.
3.	Now treat arr[i] as the largest element (c²).
4.	Use two pointers to find a pair whose sum equals arr[i]:
		left = 0
		right = i - 1
5.	If:
		arr[left] + arr[right] == arr[i]
			return true
6.	If sum < arr[i]
		move left++
7.	If sum > arr[i]
		move right--
8.	If no such triplet found after checking all elements
		return false.

	Time Complexity
	O(n²)

	Space Complexity
	O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    bool checkTriplet(vector<int>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size();

        for (int &x : arr)
            x = x * x;

        sort(arr.begin(), arr.end());

        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 2; i--) {
            int left = 0, right = i - 1;

            while (left < right) {
                int sum = arr[left] + arr[right];

                if (sum == arr[i])
                    return true;
                else if (sum < arr[i])
                    left++;
                else
                    right--;
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
};

	Key Insight
After squaring the numbers, the equation becomes a simple **two-sum problem**.
Sorting allows us to efficiently check pairs using the two-pointer technique.
